headline: Specialist interne communicatie - Corporate & Strategie - Gemeente Utrecht
summary:
Allround Marketing & Communicatie Adviseur met lange ervaring in onderwijsmarketing, customer journeys en sales funnels. Goed in het ontwikkelen van strategie√´n voor in- of externe communicatiedoelen en de vertaling naar concrete plannen en middelen. Bedreven in positionering- en profileringsvraagstukken storytelling, writing, PR, Social Media, Contentplanning- en creatie, on-en offline en e-mail marketing. Sterk in project- en teamleiding. Versatile media and communication professional with a Bachelor's degree focused in Senior Communication advising from Van der Hilst.

Guiding my clients by providing them with telematics technology solutions to increase efficiency and productivity across the workplace. I am dedicated to building, proposing, and implementing strategic solutions to my clients and vision for a strategic partnership which includes providing complete and cost-effective solutions to create an efficient workforce so our business customers can focus on what they do best!

Supporting your business in the following areas:

 - Fleet Tracking Software

Implementing technology projects takes seamless communication and execution. I have extensive experience leading organizations through these technology projects, while in turn delivering impactful solutions based on the range of Verizon‚Äôs portfolio.

Please contact me directly: Jessica.McCray@VerizonConnect.com
All Opinions Are My Own

headline: Student at University of Saskatchewan
summary:
I am a graduate of the University of Saskatchewan's bachelors of science program, majoring in biochemistry and biotechnology. From a young age I have always been fascinated with the natural world. Why does life exist? What processes govern the formation and behavior of individual organisms and how can those processes be exploited or modified in a beneficial manner?

To this end, I have completed a fair number of biomedical science courses at my university and am seeking an opportunity to apply my knowledge of the various aspects of metabolism, DNA synthesis and repair, and protein structure/function to foster a greater understanding of the world we live in, as well as make it better where I can.

2011}, 'startDate': {'month': 9, 'year': 2011}}, 'description': 'In September 2011 we embarked on one of the craziest adventures known to man - The Rickshaw Run.

Armed only with a 150cc tuk tuk and a video camera our team of three solicitors (Gareth Durnall, Richard Harris and Oliver Adams) travelled to Shillong to commence a 5000km journey to Jaisalmer with 75 other teams also competing for the coveted first place finish.

There was no route, no accommodation and no mechanic to support us although luckily Gareth did a week long orienteering trip when he was 14 and Richard had a screwdriver set from a Christmas cracker.

The aim of the adventure was to raise ¬£5000 in aid of Frank Water who will use the money to construct a sustainable water treatment station within an Indian community which will provide safe drinking water for 7000 people for life.  In a world where 4000 children die every day due to a lack of clean drinking water, it is a small price to pay.

We are pleased to report that on Tuesday 22nd September our team crossed over the finish line in second place.  We thought this was quite good considering the brakes gave up while we were heading down a national highway, the frame of the rickshaw required numerous welds due to a "minor" brush with a stationary lorry and after 1500KM the carb decided that the petrol would be better off being diverted onto the road than into the engine.

Thank you to everyone who has supported us so far and to everyone who is able to donate in some way. Through your kind donations we have managed to raise over ¬£4500 to date and with money still coming in, we hope to hit our ¬£5000 target soon.', 'title': 'Rickshaw Rally - Shillong to Jaisalmer 2011', 'url': 'http://www.justgiving.com/knightsrickshawrun'}]

headline: Financial Advisor
summary:
As a Principal at Smarter Bear Financial, I provide customized financial planning and investment management services to individuals and businesses. With over 25 years of experience in the high technology sector, I have a deep understanding of the opportunities and challenges faced by employees of SaaS, software, hardware, and digital media companies and their families.

My core competencies include financial planning, budgeting, compensation analysis, benefits planning, retirement planning and estate planning. I leverage these skills to help my clients achieve their financial goals and optimize their investments. I also hold the Certified Management Accountant (CMA) and the Series 65 credentials, which are among the best indicators of  professional standards and ethical practices.

headline: Brand Strategist, Design Thinker, Illustrator and Type Nerd
summary: Passionate about design of all sorts, I try to think of the most creative, ground-breaking and unexpected solutions for my clients. Concept is king and I see my role as a designer to be someone who injects creativity into the concept at the earliest stages possible, that way the final products are always rich with conceptual depth and more meaningful to the intended audience. I'm always looking for new awesome people to work with so please don't hesitate to reach out.

headline: Technology Leader | CTO | Engineer
summary:
As a Technology Leader, I have spent over two decades passionately forming and building great teams, building excellent products and delivering great outcomes.

My management and leadership experience includes over five years as Head of Engineering and Product Engineering in Carne Group, over three years in Kobo as Development and Delivery manager and five years in Permanent TSB as team manager. 

I am a strong people leader and truly believe that success can only be achieved by strong teamwork and collaboration. I trust and value teams, strive for fairness, and encourage a good work-life balance. I mentor, develop, and retain great people. I am highly trusted and lucky to not only retain teams, but to have worked with several of them again in different roles and companies.

I am happy helping and guiding teams through tough problems, to help find and push forward solutions. I am eager to learn and improve myself through listening, shared ideation, and feedback. The teams I lead build systems that are resilient, scalable, secure, feature rich, and dependable. They improve the lives of their users and help the business to grow.

I have a great record of helping companies through the growth phase and have taken products, platforms, and teams on journeys from proofs-of-concepts, through growth on to stable, scaled, enterprise level. I have end-of-lifed, migrated, and transitioned systems and data. 

Clean code, automated testing, good instrumentation are all crucial. Secure and safe systems are paramount. I ensure value is always delivered for not just the business, but the users. I‚Äôm an excellent bridge between highly technical and non-technical colleagues alike, and can guide differing opinions to agreement and common goals. I am as comfortable onboarding and mentoring an intern as I am pitching to boards, steer cos, or C suite.

headline: I resolve issues (legal or otherwise) creatively, commercially, and expediently.
summary:
Hearing concerns, understanding issues, providing solutions - I love doing what I do. 


Experienced general counsel with a strong track record of working across multiple jurisdictions in multi-faceted industries. 

Skilled in Regional cross-border work, Management, Change Management, Building Legal Teams, Mergers & Acquisitions, Crisis Management & Incident Response, Post-acquisition integration, Policy formulation & analysis, Service Contracts, Compliance, Transportation, Data Privacy, Supply Chain & Procurement, Channel Management, Alternative Dispute Resolution, Commercial Transactions, and Joint Ventures.

I lead a team to do this in the way I know best - from the front and with vigor (and also healthy doses of humor). 

I practice great sensitivity for local conditions and my focus is on localizing legal tools and processes so that English (as a lingua franca) doesn‚Äôt become an obstacle but a mere guidepost in order to ensure that we can all speak and work on the same frequency of solving water and effecting positive change in the world. 

I continue to work collaboratively and with a view towards ensuring harmonized, aligned, and highly contextualized legal support is provided to all; water adapts its shape to the container it is put in - I believe legal support should be as flexible.

headline: Property Adminstrator
summary:
I am a proven leader in the security and law enforcement industry, having gained over 20 years‚Äô experience in investigative services and security management. My areas of expertise range from private estate management to emergency medical care to international security. I founded my own private investigation company, Dunn Executive Services, in 2016.

My experience is grounded in heading and training teams of security staff, organizing executive protection services for prominent families and their private residences, as well as managing the budget and financial concerns of the properties that I protect. I am skilled in collaborating with employees and colleagues to achieve business and financial objectives on time and within budget. 

My work in high-risk security and law enforcement environments has shaped me into a confident team leader who works well under pressure and excels in personnel management. I am firmly committed the cause of justice and to protecting my clients through effective security services.

To learn more, please connect with me or send me an InMail.

headline: Director of DTC at Gibson Brands
summary:
Growth hacking certified DTC Digital Marketing & eCommerce Director with over 10 years of experience of UK and international marketing. Managing pan-European performance marketing including, paid social, paid search, display, YouTube SEO, affiliates to encourage direct eCommerce conversion, revenue growth and brand awareness. Passionate about web development confidently managing complex integration projects to deliver exceptional results on time and within budget. Experienced team leader and people manager.

My mission in life is to keep learning and growing my knowledge, both personally and professionally. I am excited about new challenges and love to tackle problems head on with a cool head and calm demeanor imparting skills and knowledge to direct reports and other professionals.
